<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title></title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">General Medical Council </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">(</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">CQ 08)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The General Medical Council (GMC) is the independent regulator for doctors in the UK. Our role is to protect patients by ensuring proper standards in the practice of medicine. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We do this by controlling entry to the medical register and setting the standards for medical schools and postgraduate education and training. We also determine the principles and values that underpin good medical practice and we take firm but fair action where those standards have not been met </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> if necessary, by removing the doctor from the register and removing their right to practise medicine.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In this memorandum we summarise how we are working together with the CQC to protect patients as well as our response to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">their strategy for 2013</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2016</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 14pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Partnership working with the CQC</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The GMC and CQC are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">both part of a wider system of healthcare regulation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> committed to improving the quality and safety of care. The Francis Report </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">set a clear challenge that we should work more closely together and we are determined to do so.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Given the breadth of CQC’s functions and the richness of its data and insights, it is important that the GMC and other professional regulators regularly engage with CQC in all aspects of their work including strategy, operational planning, inspections and visits, data sharing and risk analysis.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Building on our Memoranda of Understanding with the CQC, we have put in place practical arrangements to facilitate our commitments. A joint operational protocol was agreed in September 2013 which sets out </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">key contacts at both organisations, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">when and how we will share our respective information in order to improve the way we protect patients and identify risks.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We are already more proactively sharing information with the CQC, such as our complaints information, hearing decisions, revalidation decisions and national training survey data.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Similarly, the CQC shares information with us which informs our investigations and education quality assurance functions. We also work with each other at risk summits and regional quality surveillance groups. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We have also recently provided data from across our functions to inform the first wave of the new model CQC inspections at the NHS Trusts that were investigated by Professor Sir Bruce Keogh.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Over the next few months there will be a series of training events for GMC and CQC staff who work in teams that will be using the protocol regularly. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We are developing a joint approach to the evaluation of the operating protocol. An interim evaluation is scheduled for September 2014 and a full evaluation in September 2015.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 14pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Our response to the CQC’s strategy for 2013</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">–</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2016</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We are supportive of the proposals set out by the CQC in their recent consultation on their strategy for 2013</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2016. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">believe that the intention and approach reflect our organisations’ shared commitment for the healthcare regulatory system in England to be transparent, accountable,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">proportionate, consistent, and targeted at protecting patients.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The CQC and GMC have a common interest in ensuring that healthcare organisations have good clinical governance arrangements in place. This has become all the more important with the Responsible Officer regulations coming into legal effect in 2011. All healthcare organisations are now required to appoint a Responsible Officer whose responsibilities include making revalidation recommendations, ensuring that the organisation carries out appraisals of its doctors and implementing procedures for investigating concerns about doctors. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Building on our shared approach, we have in our response to their consultation recommended that an explicit CQC judgment on compliance with the Responsible Officer regulations be included as a key component of the ‘well led’ assessment of a healthcare provider.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 14pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Our full response to this consultation can be found on our website</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 14pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">October 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 18pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:9pt">http://www.gmc-uk.org/GMC_response_CQC___A_New_Start_consultation_August_2013.pdf_53072994.pdf</span></p></body></html>